01:05:27.660 --> 01:05:29.660
And it is Pearl Jam.

01:05:29.660 --> 01:05:30.660
So we're on?

01:05:30.660 --> 01:05:31.660
We're on.

01:05:32.660 --> 01:05:34.660
Hey, what's all this stuff for?

01:05:34.660 --> 01:05:36.660
Just stuff I'm going to do with my grandparents.

01:05:36.660 --> 01:05:39.660
Wow, I never plan to do anything with my grandpa.

01:05:39.660 --> 01:05:41.660
He just rests all the time.

01:05:41.660 --> 01:05:42.660
It's like a hobby.

01:05:42.660 --> 01:05:45.660
He eats breakfast, reads the paper and takes a nap.

01:05:46.660 --> 01:05:50.660
Gets up for lunch, watches the Perry Mason rerun and takes a nap.

01:05:50.660 --> 01:05:52.660
Then it's time for people's court a little dinner and...

01:05:52.660 --> 01:05:54.660
Another nap?

01:05:54.660 --> 01:05:56.660
No, then it's pretty much bedtime.

01:05:56.660 --> 01:05:59.660
Well, it's not like I've scheduled bungee jumping, Sam.

01:05:59.660 --> 01:06:02.660
Besides, their idea of an aerobic workout

01:06:02.660 --> 01:06:04.660
is shuffling the cards before another round of rummy.

01:06:04.660 --> 01:06:07.660
Yeah, my grandpa loves to play cards too.

01:06:07.660 --> 01:06:09.660
We play for pretzel sticks.

01:06:09.660 --> 01:06:12.660
It's always quit eating the pot, Tike.

01:06:12.660 --> 01:06:13.660
Tike?

01:06:13.660 --> 01:06:15.660
It's his dumb pet name for me.

01:06:15.660 --> 01:06:18.660
Put it there, Tike. How ya doin', Tike?

01:06:18.660 --> 01:06:21.660
I'm permanently fixed in his brain as being four years old.

01:06:21.660 --> 01:06:23.660
They enjoy babying you.

01:06:23.660 --> 01:06:26.660
So, grandparents, it's part of their job description.

01:06:26.660 --> 01:06:27.660
No kidding.

01:06:27.660 --> 01:06:30.660
At Christmas, he sent me a Mr. Potato Head with a note to my dad

01:06:30.660 --> 01:06:32.660
to make sure I don't swallow any of the small pieces.

01:06:32.660 --> 01:06:34.660
Come on, you're exaggerating.

01:06:34.660 --> 01:06:35.660
Oh, yeah?

01:06:35.660 --> 01:06:38.660
Last time they were here, they took me to see Rafi, eighth row center.

01:06:38.660 --> 01:06:39.660
Hmm.

01:06:39.660 --> 01:06:43.660
Eighth row for Rafi, second balcony for Pearl Jam.

01:06:43.660 --> 01:06:45.660
What's wrong with this picture?

01:06:45.660 --> 01:06:51.890
I believe you're making pot roast, Mom.

01:06:51.890 --> 01:06:53.890
Believe me, it wasn't my idea,

01:06:53.890 --> 01:06:56.890
but your grandparents have to have red meat every day.

01:06:56.890 --> 01:06:58.890
It's just too bad, Grandma and Grandpa

01:06:58.890 --> 01:07:00.890
haven't discovered the benefits of health foods.

01:07:00.890 --> 01:07:03.890
You just have to suffer through it and pretend we like it.

01:07:03.890 --> 01:07:06.300
Yes!

01:07:06.300 --> 01:07:07.300
Where are they?

01:07:07.300 --> 01:07:10.300
They're late. They're never late.

01:07:10.300 --> 01:07:11.300
But they're late.

01:07:11.300 --> 01:07:12.300
Marshall, I'm sure they're fine.

01:07:12.300 --> 01:07:13.300
And so is the pot roast.

01:07:13.300 --> 01:07:15.300
I've already seasoned it with herbs. I think they'll like it.

01:07:15.300 --> 01:07:16.300
Well, let's make sure.

01:07:16.300 --> 01:07:17.300
Marshall!

01:07:17.300 --> 01:07:19.300
Janet, can we just do this?

01:07:19.300 --> 01:07:20.300
I do not want to sit through two hours

01:07:20.300 --> 01:07:22.300
and my parents telling us the right way to make pot roast.

01:07:22.300 --> 01:07:25.300
Chill out, Dad. It's just beef.

01:07:25.300 --> 01:07:27.300
Well, you try telling them that.

01:07:27.300 --> 01:07:29.300
If you're going to get this upset over a pot roast,

01:07:29.300 --> 01:07:31.300
how are you going to handle their anniversary?

01:07:31.300 --> 01:07:33.300
You're right.

01:07:33.300 --> 01:07:34.300
I know.

01:07:34.300 --> 01:07:37.800
It just doesn't matter what I do.

01:07:37.800 --> 01:07:39.800
They find it too radical.

01:07:39.800 --> 01:07:41.800
When I had my hair long, they wanted it short.

01:07:41.800 --> 01:07:43.800
My major in architecture, they wanted an accountant.

01:07:43.800 --> 01:07:45.800
I had my own rock and roll band,

01:07:45.800 --> 01:07:48.800
and they told me to play the cello.

01:07:48.800 --> 01:07:50.800
Forget about politics.

01:07:50.800 --> 01:07:52.800
Well, they are a little straight-laced.

01:07:52.800 --> 01:07:54.800
I just wish they would loosen up a little.

01:07:54.800 --> 01:07:55.800
They're so conservative.

01:07:55.800 --> 01:07:57.800
My kind of people.

01:07:57.800 --> 01:07:59.800
Your kind of people are slimy with fins.

01:07:59.800 --> 01:08:00.800
Slug.

01:08:00.800 --> 01:08:01.800
Come on back.

01:08:01.800 --> 01:08:02.800
Hold it.

01:08:02.800 --> 01:08:04.800
There will be none of that.

01:08:04.800 --> 01:08:05.800
For the week my parents are here,

01:08:05.800 --> 01:08:06.800
there will be peace and quiet,

01:08:06.800 --> 01:08:07.800
not too much excitement,

01:08:07.800 --> 01:08:09.800
not too much stress.

01:08:09.800 --> 01:08:11.800
Well, they'll probably be worn out

01:08:11.800 --> 01:08:13.800
from the trip anyway.

01:08:13.800 --> 01:08:15.800
Finally.

01:08:15.800 --> 01:08:16.800
All right.

01:08:16.800 --> 01:08:17.800
Okay.

01:08:17.800 --> 01:08:18.800
They're here.

01:08:18.800 --> 01:08:19.800
Okay.

01:08:19.800 --> 01:08:20.800
Is everything okay?

01:08:20.800 --> 01:08:21.800
Is the meat okay?

01:08:21.800 --> 01:08:27.570
Do I look okay?

01:08:27.570 --> 01:08:28.570
Uh-huh.

01:08:28.570 --> 01:08:29.570
Wartlet.

01:08:29.570 --> 01:08:30.570
Hey, hey.

01:08:30.570 --> 01:08:31.570
Now, remember what I said.

01:08:31.570 --> 01:08:50.590
I know everybody's excited, but...

01:08:50.590 --> 01:08:51.590
Hey, Slugger.

01:08:51.590 --> 01:08:53.590
Um, where were you?

01:08:53.590 --> 01:08:55.590
Yes, we were beginning to worry.

01:08:55.590 --> 01:08:57.590
Nat, a popper, don't you want to sit down?

01:08:57.590 --> 01:08:58.590
Hold on, hold on.

01:08:58.590 --> 01:08:59.590
I'll tense up.

01:08:59.590 --> 01:09:00.590
I have to work out.

01:09:00.590 --> 01:09:01.590
It's best to keep moving and stay loose.

01:09:01.590 --> 01:09:02.590
Work out?

01:09:02.590 --> 01:09:04.590
Well, we drove by the old high school and went in.

01:09:04.590 --> 01:09:06.590
Oh, you know it looks a lot smaller.

01:09:06.590 --> 01:09:08.590
We just had to get out and shoot a few hoops.

01:09:08.590 --> 01:09:09.590
Hoops?

01:09:09.590 --> 01:09:11.590
As in basketball?

01:09:11.590 --> 01:09:13.590
They're joking.

01:09:13.590 --> 01:09:14.590
You are joking, right?

01:09:14.590 --> 01:09:16.590
Listen, I still get a few moves left, yeah.

01:09:16.590 --> 01:09:18.590
I can't believe you guys played basketball.

01:09:18.590 --> 01:09:20.590
Oh, we're not full court.

01:09:20.590 --> 01:09:23.590
Slowpoke here can't handle my fast break.

01:09:26.590 --> 01:09:28.590
Well, what's the matter?

01:09:28.590 --> 01:09:30.590
Why is everybody so quiet?

01:09:30.590 --> 01:09:32.590
Somebody die around here?

01:09:32.590 --> 01:09:33.590
I'm famished.

01:09:33.590 --> 01:09:34.590
Come on, Amelia.

01:09:34.590 --> 01:09:35.590
Let's go wash up for dinner.

01:09:35.590 --> 01:09:37.590
Last one up the stairs buys a Gatorade.

01:09:37.590 --> 01:09:39.590
Oh, you're off.

01:09:39.590 --> 01:09:46.540
I have just one question, Dad.

01:09:46.540 --> 01:09:48.540
What's that, sport?

01:09:48.540 --> 01:09:51.540
What have those people done with our real grandparents?

01:09:51.540 --> 01:09:56.080
I'm sorry about the pot roast mixed up, Janet.

01:09:56.080 --> 01:09:58.080
Oh, well, I could have prepared a vegetarian banquet

01:09:58.080 --> 01:10:01.080
if only I'd known you'd given up red meat.

01:10:01.080 --> 01:10:03.080
And caffeine.

01:10:03.080 --> 01:10:05.080
And sugar.

01:10:05.080 --> 01:10:07.080
And white flour.

01:10:07.080 --> 01:10:09.080
Oh, toxins.

01:10:09.080 --> 01:10:11.080
That's what they are.

01:10:11.080 --> 01:10:13.080
Those things will kill you.

01:10:13.080 --> 01:10:15.080
Nana, Papa, what happened to you?

01:10:15.080 --> 01:10:16.080
Clarissa?

01:10:16.080 --> 01:10:19.080
No, I'd like an answer to that, too, huh?

01:10:19.080 --> 01:10:22.080
It's just that you both seem so...

01:10:22.080 --> 01:10:24.080
Well, go ahead and say it.

01:10:24.080 --> 01:10:26.080
Young.

01:10:26.080 --> 01:10:28.080
We feel marvelous.

01:10:28.080 --> 01:10:30.080
Sure do.

01:10:30.080 --> 01:10:32.080
This is too weird.

01:10:32.080 --> 01:10:34.080
You guys aren't the same people who sent me

01:10:34.080 --> 01:10:37.080
my first subscription to the Wall Street Journal.

01:10:37.080 --> 01:10:39.080
Yeah, Dad, I mean, you didn't act like this

01:10:39.080 --> 01:10:40.080
before you were retired.

01:10:40.080 --> 01:10:42.080
Yeah, a guy knew what to expect then.

01:10:42.080 --> 01:10:43.080
What went wrong?

01:10:43.080 --> 01:10:46.080
Well, I'll tell you, for 42 years I ran my factory.

01:10:46.080 --> 01:10:48.080
And all we ever made was those little

01:10:48.080 --> 01:10:51.080
press-on nose pads for eyeglasses.

01:10:51.080 --> 01:10:53.080
Four-ring!

01:10:53.080 --> 01:10:56.080
So we were really looking forward to our golden years.

01:10:56.080 --> 01:10:58.080
Time to play cards.

01:10:58.080 --> 01:11:00.080
Yes, watch old movies.

01:11:00.080 --> 01:11:02.080
Look at the birds.

01:11:02.080 --> 01:11:04.080
Sounds great.

01:11:04.080 --> 01:11:05.080
Was it great?

01:11:05.080 --> 01:11:07.080
He was driving me up the wall,

01:11:07.080 --> 01:11:09.080
but he couldn't sit still.

01:11:09.080 --> 01:11:11.080
It was depressing.

01:11:11.080 --> 01:11:12.080
Then it hit me.

01:11:12.080 --> 01:11:14.080
Last June we were playing cards.

01:11:14.080 --> 01:11:17.080
I hate Jen Rummy.

01:11:17.080 --> 01:11:20.080
To tell the truth, I always hated Jen Rummy.

01:11:20.080 --> 01:11:23.080
Well, I only played it because he liked it.

01:11:23.080 --> 01:11:26.080
That's when we decided to live a little.

01:11:26.080 --> 01:11:29.080
And we've been on the go ever since.

01:11:29.080 --> 01:11:31.080
Well, I think that's wonderful.

01:11:31.080 --> 01:11:33.080
I think it's awful.

01:11:33.080 --> 01:11:36.080
I mean, I'm often nice.

01:11:36.080 --> 01:11:39.080
I think it's, you know, I think it's...

01:11:39.080 --> 01:11:41.080
Hey.

01:11:41.080 --> 01:11:44.080
I think I'd better replay my week.

01:11:44.080 --> 01:11:47.080
Well, out with the old and in with the new.

01:11:47.080 --> 01:11:50.080
It's great to see you can get older without getting slower.

01:11:50.080 --> 01:11:52.080
The only thing is, if they keep up this pace,

01:11:52.080 --> 01:11:54.080
who knows what'll happen.

01:11:54.080 --> 01:11:57.080
Will their search for adventure have a scaling new height?

01:11:57.080 --> 01:12:03.760
Will that collection needs a little more zip?

01:12:03.760 --> 01:12:16.540
Or will they become international spies?

01:12:16.540 --> 01:12:19.540
Boiling plots for global domination.

01:12:22.540 --> 01:12:24.540
I thought I'd have to set the pace for them,

01:12:24.540 --> 01:12:27.540
but now it looks like they're setting the pace for me.

01:12:27.540 --> 01:12:34.630
And my whole family.

01:12:34.630 --> 01:12:36.630
What a week.

01:12:36.630 --> 01:12:39.630
It's been nonstop ever since my grandparents got here.

01:12:39.630 --> 01:12:41.630
We spent Monday at the water park,

01:12:41.630 --> 01:12:43.630
Tuesday at the blues festival,

01:12:43.630 --> 01:12:45.630
Wednesday night square dancing,

01:12:45.630 --> 01:12:47.630
and today it was Wismos Arcade.

01:12:47.630 --> 01:12:51.630
We've got blown away, soaked, trampled, and blasted.

01:12:51.630 --> 01:12:53.630
I never felt better.

01:12:53.630 --> 01:12:55.630
In fact, aside from my grandparents,

01:12:55.630 --> 01:12:57.630
I'm the only one still standing.

01:12:57.630 --> 01:12:59.630
Chief, watch.

01:12:59.630 --> 01:13:01.630
I can't believe the prizes they give out.

01:13:01.630 --> 01:13:03.630
It does nothing it's supposed to.

01:13:03.630 --> 01:13:06.630
It's a two dollar watch. It did everything it's supposed to.

01:13:06.630 --> 01:13:14.810
It broke.

01:13:14.810 --> 01:13:16.810
Am I holding the keys?

01:13:16.810 --> 01:13:18.810
Oh good, I wasn't sure.

01:13:18.810 --> 01:13:22.810
I've lost all feeling in my arm after four straight hours of ski ball.

01:13:22.810 --> 01:13:25.810
Well no one can say you're not a good sport, Marshall.

01:13:25.810 --> 01:13:27.810
What has happened to my parents?

01:13:27.810 --> 01:13:29.810
I mean, I can't get over the change.

01:13:29.810 --> 01:13:32.810
Remember when they came to visit last year?

01:13:32.810 --> 01:13:35.810
We spent the whole week doing that 900 piece jigsaw puzzle

01:13:35.810 --> 01:13:37.810
of a covered bridge.

01:13:37.810 --> 01:13:39.810
Now those are the days.

01:13:39.810 --> 01:13:41.810
See you then.

01:13:41.810 --> 01:13:43.810
It's no longer sad.

01:13:43.810 --> 01:13:45.810
It's great to see the Belmondos again, huh?

01:13:45.810 --> 01:13:47.810
Oh still, the same old friend and baby.

01:13:47.810 --> 01:13:51.810
Oh and they're so excited about the party Saturday night.

01:13:51.810 --> 01:13:53.810
Saturday night?

01:13:53.810 --> 01:13:55.810
What party Saturday night?

01:13:55.810 --> 01:13:58.810
Crossing your grandparents' anniversary party.

01:13:58.810 --> 01:14:01.810
I thought that was on the 18th.

01:14:01.810 --> 01:14:04.810
Saturday is the 18th Brainiac.

01:14:05.810 --> 01:14:08.810
You have plans?

01:14:08.810 --> 01:14:12.810
Well, I was just going to go see Pearl Jam.

01:14:12.810 --> 01:14:16.810
Well, you can invite your friend Pearl to the party.

01:14:16.810 --> 01:14:19.810
Yeah, so we still have our DJ.

01:14:19.810 --> 01:14:23.500
Yeah, you can count on me.

01:14:23.500 --> 01:14:25.500
Any special requests?

01:14:25.500 --> 01:14:28.500
Well, my favorite band is Vanilla Fudge.

01:14:28.500 --> 01:14:31.500
How can you listen to that stuff?

01:14:31.500 --> 01:14:40.160
Decisions, decisions.

01:14:40.160 --> 01:14:44.160
There's so much music to choose from when you're trying to please three generations.

01:14:44.160 --> 01:14:46.160
I guess one thing I won't be hearing is Pearl Jam.

01:14:46.160 --> 01:14:48.160
But Sam's tickets were crummy anyway.

01:14:48.160 --> 01:14:50.160
There'll be other concerts.

01:14:50.160 --> 01:14:52.160
Hi Sam.

01:14:52.160 --> 01:14:56.400
Hey, Clarissa. Guess what?

01:14:56.400 --> 01:14:57.400
What?

01:14:57.400 --> 01:14:59.400
My dad came through for us.

01:14:59.400 --> 01:15:03.400
It seems the music editor really wanted basketball tickets only my dad could get hold of.

01:15:03.400 --> 01:15:04.400
So?

01:15:04.400 --> 01:15:06.400
So?

01:15:06.400 --> 01:15:09.400
Pearl Jam Fourth Row Center.

01:15:09.400 --> 01:15:11.400
We totally scored.

01:15:11.400 --> 01:15:13.400
Fourth row?

01:15:13.400 --> 01:15:15.400
Fourth row from the stage?

01:15:15.400 --> 01:15:16.400
Yeah, can you believe it?

01:15:16.400 --> 01:15:19.400
This is going to be one totally awesome event.

01:15:19.400 --> 01:15:23.060
One totally awesome event too many.

01:15:23.060 --> 01:15:25.060
Now what am I going to do?

